                                    ••
                                 pſhire, contrary to ſeveral Treaties heretofore ſolemnly entred into: And the ſaid Indians being now ſenſible of the Miſeries and Troubles they have involved themſelves in, and being deſirous to be reſtured to His Majeſty's Grace and Favour, and to live in Peace with all His Majeſty's Subjects; and that all former Acts of Injury may be fogotten;
